/*!
\page trademgen_with_db
      Database-enabled C++ Simulated Travel Demand Generation Library

\section sec_synopsis SYNOPSIS

<b>trademgen_with_db</b> <tt>[--prefix] [-v|--version] [-h|--help] [-b|--builtin] [-i|--input <path-to-input>] [-l|--log <path-to-output-log-file>]</tt>

\section sec_description DESCRIPTION

\e trademgen_with_db is the database-enabled version of the \e trademgen
   executable, i.e., a small program showing how to use the TraDemGen library.

\e trademgen_with_db accepts the following options:

 \b --prefix<br>
    Show the TraDemGen installation prefix.<br>

 \b -v, \b --version<br>
    Print the currently installed version of TraDemGen on the standard
    output.<br>

 \b -h, \b --help<br>
    Produce that message and show usage.<br>

 \b -b, \b --builtin<br>
    The sample BOM tree can be either built-in or parsed from an input
    file.  That latter must then be given with the -i/--input option.<br>

 \b -s, \b --see<br>
    Seed for the random generation. It allows to reproduce exactly any
    demand generation.<br>

 \b -d, \b --draws
    Number of runs for the demand generation.<br>

 \b -G, \b --demandgeneration
    Method used to generate the demand (i.e., the booking requests):
    Poisson Process (P) or Order Statistics (S).<br>

 \b -i, \b --input <path-to-input-file><br>
    Path (absolute or relative) of the (CSV) input file specifying
    the demand rule sets.<br>

 \b -l, \b --log <path-to-output-log-file><br>
    Path (absolute or relative) of the output log file.<br>

 \b -u, \b --user <database-user-name><br>
    SQL database user (e.g., dsim).<br>

 \b -p, \b --passwd <database-user-password><br>
    SQL database password (e.g., dsim).<br>

 \b -H, \b --host <database-server-host-name><br>
    SQL database hostname (e.g., localhost).<br>

 \b -P, \b --port <database-server-port><br>
    SQL database port (e.g., 3306).<br>

 \b -m, \b --dbname <database-name><br>
    SQL database name (e.g., sim_dsim).<br>

See the output of the <tt>`trademgen_with_db --help'</tt> command for 
default options.


